umlet.io/uploads/eb/eb28e744481edeea4c8026050f7fbc74.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/eb/eb28e744481edeea4c8026050f7fbc74.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/eb/eb28e744481edeea4c8026050f7fbc74.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/eb/eb28e744481edeea4c8026050f7fbc74.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: courtesy Tim Griffith\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a5/a57099c51a8068f23206ed2acf8ad83b.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x914\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a5/a57099c51a8068f23206ed2acf8ad83b.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a5/a57099c51a8068f23206ed2acf8ad83b.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a5/a57099c51a8068f23206ed2acf8ad83b.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a5/a57099c51a8068f23206ed2acf8ad83b.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: courtesy Tim Griffith\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u0026#34;This isn’t just a storage facility for the departed,\u0026#34; founder Michael Lehrer explained to the \u003cem\u003eLA Times\u003c/em\u003e recently. \u0026#34;It’s about making a place for the living to connect with the past while being inspired by their surroundings.\u0026#34; As Lehrer mentions, the design of the structure offers a contiguous connection with the neighboring soundstage elevations of Paramount Studios, which form the southern half of the newly revitalized full city block.  \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/20/20f907864fec89106d86e1f9349f99d0.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x801\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/20/20f907864fec89106d86e1f9349f99d0.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/20/20f907864fec89106d86e1f9349f99d0.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/20/20f907864fec89106d86e1f9349f99d0.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/20/20f907864fec89106d86e1f9349f99d0.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: courtesy Tim Griffith\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/5b/5bf714de72af3d8aab1182d4189cc9f2.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x794\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/5b/5bf714de72af3d8aab1182d4189cc9f2.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/5b/5bf714de72af3d8aab1182d4189cc9f2.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/5b/5bf714de72af3d8aab1182d4189cc9f2.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/5b/5bf714de72af3d8aab1182d4189cc9f2.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: courtesy Tim Griffith\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eHe was working with his former colleague Robert Sheinberg, the former Principal-in-Charge who left the firm to found Arquitectura y Diseño (or AyD) in 2021. Lehrer Architects has been working closely with Hollywood Forever since 2013, when it was first conceived as a project that would help extend the cemetery\u0026#39;s service life by another fifty years.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/ec/ec4c51b0b8ada49dfc6b26d3351f00d9.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x1415\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/ec/ec4c51b0b8ada49dfc6b26d3351f00d9.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/ec/ec4c51b0b8ada49dfc6b26d3351f00d9.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/ec/ec4c51b0b8ada49dfc6b26d3351f00d9.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/ec/ec4c51b0b8ada49dfc6b26d3351f00d9.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: courtesy Tim Griffith\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/firms/cover/22201405/studio-mla-formerly-mia-lehrer-associates\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eStudio-MLA\u003c/a\u003e’s landscape contribution completes the design beginning at the ground level, serving visitors with a lush \u0026#34;reminder of the enduring and the ephemeral\u0026#34; that forms vertically until culminating at the roof garden and promenade beset by the granite block Columbarium and Information Center. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/d5/d5c8712f22950203e70f089517d52d6c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x791\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/d5/d5c8712f22950203e70f089517d52d6c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/d5/d5c8712f22950203e70f089517d52d6c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/d5/d5c8712f22950203e70f089517d52d6c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/d5/d5c8712f22950203e70f089517d52d6c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: courtesy Tim Griffith\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003ePhase 1, which includes 5,000 crypts and 8,000 niches was completed over 4.5 years. Phase 2 will begin construction in the spring of 2025, adding a further 6,500 crypts and another 10,000 niches. Phase 3 will follow with 10,000 more crypts and 12,000 niches to complete the 400-foot-long, 160,000-square-foot structure. \u003c/p\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cbr clear=\"all\"/\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ca name=\"comments\" 